# KASAN overlay fragment — merged ON TOP of tutorial.config to build a SEPARATE
# kernel for the optional lesson C2 (harness/build-kasan-kernel.sh). It is NEVER
# merged into the base tutorial kernel: KASAN is a debug/CI build (high overhead),
# so in real life you build a dedicated KASAN kernel to chase a memory bug — which
# is exactly what this overlay models.
#
# Generic KASAN = software shadow memory (1 shadow byte per 8 bytes), the precise,
# x86_64-capable flavor used by syzkaller/CI. Outline mode keeps the image smaller
# (a call per check) at some speed cost — fine for a tiny tutorial guest.
CONFIG_KASAN=y
CONFIG_KASAN_GENERIC=y
CONFIG_KASAN_OUTLINE=y
# Stack traces in the report — the "Allocated by task" / "Freed by task" stacks.
CONFIG_STACKTRACE=y
CONFIG_DEBUG_KERNEL=y
